sparent; display: inline-block;"></div></ins></div>
<p>Note how there is indeed a subtle change for the smallest focal lengths.=
 This is a real effect, but is negligible compared to both aperture and foc=
using distance. Even though the total depth of field is virtually constant,=
 the fraction of the depth of field which is in front of and behind the foc=
us distance does change with focal length, as demonstrated below:</p>
<div class=3D"center">
<table class=3D"t1 pad">
<tbody><tr>
<td class=3D"bg">&nbsp;</td>
